Author: Maksym Bondarenko [aut, cre, cph] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4958-6551>),
  Jeremiah J. Nieves [aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7423-134>),
  David Kerr [aut],
  Alessandro Sorichetta (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3576-5826>)
Maintainer: Maksym Bondarenko <mb4@soton.ac.uk>    
Description: Disaggregating census-based areal population counts to finer 
    gridded population surfaces using Random Forest algorithm to determine 
    the target area weights. For more information about the method, read a paper 
    Stevens et al. (2015) DOI: 10.1371/journal.pone.0107042.
URL: https://sdi.worldpop.org
BugReports: https://github.com/wpgp/popRF/issues
Imports: doParallel, parallel, raster, methods, stats, foreach, gdalUtils, randomForest, quantregForest, snow, plyr
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
